The MRF-CX is designed to install on a standard factory M4 barrel, the mounting system reinforces the factory barrel nut and the anti-rotational tabs keep everything tight. title: For Sale:  Browning Hi-Power
postcontent: For sale is my personal custom Browning Hi-Power 9mm pistol in excellent condition. It is a Browning-manufactured Mark III pistol that was sent to a professional gunsmith for a very slight blending of corners and sharp edges (aka street bevel) which makes holstering easier and less damaging. After that, it was sent out for Birdsong’s famous Black-T coating (this one has NATO Green-T with Black-T accents). This is the coating that Birdsong put on HK MP5s for the US Navy. It is very corrosion-resistant and naturally lubricious; it does not require an oily lubricant that attracts debris. I do use a bit of Frog Lube anyway, and any appearance of stains in a picture are due to lubricant. I probably haven’t shot 100 rounds through this pistol, and it never had a malfunction. It shoots straight and looks great. It is about 25 years old and has just been sitting in my safe for the last 20 years. Time to go to someone who will use it. Included are 4 magazines: two Green-T MecGar mags, one Black-T MecGar, and one Black-T original Browning mag. All hold 13 rounds. Hogue grips. Sell F2F to AL CCP holder.

title: For Sale:  M1 Garand for sale
location: Fredericksburg, northern or central Virginia, Virginia, United States
postcontent:
Beautiful M1 Garand for sale.  This is exactly how a classic M1, WW 2 era Garand should look and shoot.  Beautiful color!  The receiver was made in late November of 1943, and the rifle underwent an arsenal rebuild sometime in mid 1945 based on the barrel date of April 45.  The trigger housing and all trigger group components are SA except for the trigger guard, which is WRA.  The op rod is a D35382-6 SA with the relief cut, which is the correct op rod for the serial number of the rifle.  The stock is a SA EMcF stock (cartouche is very, very, very faint) and has a RA-P (Raritan Arsenal) arsenal stamp added.  While the stock isn't "correct" for the rifle serial number, it is a USGI stock and in excellent shape for being 60 years old - and it has the dings that a battle rifle stock should display. 
 
I have shot this rifle and it shoots like a champ.  The barrel reading are TE2+, ME1+, which are extremely good.  Please contact me and we'll arrange for a place to meet and look at the rifle.  I bought this rifle from the individual who purchased it from CMP.  I have the original issued CMP certificate.  Also includes several extra clips!
